# .pairmode-overrides — Sections intentionally diverged from canonical pairmode templates.
#
# Audit and sync will treat declared sections as project-owned (EXTRA) rather than
# INCONSISTENT or MISSING. Sync will never overwrite a declared override section.
#
# Format: one entry per line — <relative-file-path>:<normalised-section-key>
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# The section key is the full header line — `##` markers included — lowercased and
# whitespace-collapsed. Examples below match this format.
# Examples:
#   CLAUDE.md:## review checklist
#   .claude/agents/reviewer.md:### checklist
#   .claude/agents/reviewer.md:**3. build gate**
#
# Bold numbered checklist markers (e.g. `**3. BUILD GATE**`, `**5a. Conviction
# consistency**`) are also valid, independently addressable section keys — this
# lets you pin a single checklist item without opting the whole enclosing `##`
# section out of future canonical updates.
#
# Note: `.pairmode-overrides` is honored by `pairmode sync` (scaffold sync) and
# `audit`, but NOT by `pairmode sync-build`. `sync-build --apply` rewrites
# CLAUDE.build.md wholesale and ignores these declarations. Maintain CLAUDE.build.md
# via surgical merge, never via `sync-build --apply`.
